                  </persName>
             the prisoner there at that time? - He was.</p>
               <p>Grubb. My Lord, I saw Doharty there, he came to appear on the behalf of Burton.</p>
               <p>Doharty ordered to be committed to Newgate, for wilful and corrupt perjury, and Grubb and Macmanus, bound over to prosecute him.</p>
